        "title": "Leaving Crockett",
        "description": "In September of 1988, Arn Anderson & Tully Blanchard left Jim Crockett Promotions to join the World Wrestling Federation. In this episode we examine all of the details surrounding that decision. The whos, hows, whys, and whens are broken down in great detail for the first time ever. You'll hear specifics of what exactly was frustrating half of the Horsemen, when it started, why they stayed as long as they did, and what ultimately led to their departure. Was it cash? Or was it creative? Who reached out to who in order to make this jump happen? When did Arn meet Vince? What was the meeting like? What did Flair think when he found out they were leaving? What did Dusty say when they gave notice? Plus we \"fantasy book\" if Arn and Tully hadn't left when and how they did. If you're looking for lots of specifics and details never before revealed about the end of Jim Crockett Promotions, this is the episode for you!\nThe easiest way to support the show is to subscribe, leave a review, and tell a friend! www.ArnShow.com has the direct link to listen online or just tell a friend to search for \"ARN\" anywhere they enjoy podcasts.\nThe next best way to support the show is to buy a shirt and get a call from Arn: www.ArnShirts.com\nDon't miss the first live ARN in North Carolina 11/30: www.ArnShowLive.com\nMeet Arn, the Superstars of AEW, and all of the great talent from yesteryear in Baltimore 11/7-11/10: www.Starrcast.com\nSave yourself some money by consolidating your debt and getting a lower mortgage payment: www.SaveWithConrad.com",
