        "description": "After more than thirty years, the Founder of the Four Horsemen is finally giving you a peek behind the curtain. In Episode One of ARN, the Enforcer starts at the beginning of his journey into professional wrestling. Was he a fan growing up and if so, what did he grow up watching? What was his athletic background before wrestling? How did he get into the business? Who trained him? What was his first territory? How did we move around from territory to territory? How did he decide where to live and with whom? Who did he ride with? Who was his biggest influence when he was first getting started? How did he decide on a name? How did he become an Anderson? What was up with the hat? What was his favorite territory and why? How did he land in Jim Crockett Promotions?\nSee our very first live show on 11/30 at WrestleCade after the matches: www.ArnShowLive.com \nPick up a new ARN or Horsemen shirt today and get a call from Double A: www.ArnShirts.com\nGive your gimmick the \"hot tag\" and bust some spines at www.BlueChew.com and use promo code ARN to get your first order FREE, just pay $5 shipping!\nDDT your debt at www.SaveWithConrad.com\nHave a question for next week's show about leaving Crockett for the WWF? Just follow us on Twitter, @TheArnShow !",
