        "title": "The Curtain Call",
        "description": "It's considered one of the most controversial moments in WWE history, still, to this very day! It's \"The Curtain Call,\" when five of the biggest superstars of all time, embraced following the main event at a WWE house show at Madison Square Garden, and Jim Ross is here to discuss it at length! Razor Ramon (Scott Hall) and Diesel (Kevin Nash) were on their way out the door to WCW, and this was their send off from their buddies in The Kliq, Shawn Michaels and Triple H. Two were heels, two were babyfaces, yet here they were. breaking kayfabe, in the middle of Vince McMahon's WWE ring, on hallowed ground. What was the feeling of upper management and the other wrestlers before, during, and after this took place? What should the consequences have been, and more! Plus, discussion about stars like Steve Austin, Bret Hart, Sean Waltman, and The Ultimate Warrior at this time, as well as talk about the looming WCW threat!\n\nRate/subscribe in Apple Podcasts! \n\nNew episodes every Thursday at 6 AM\n\nHit JR on Twitter: @JRsBBQ\n\nFind JR on Facebook/Instagram: @JimRossBBQ",
