        "title": "Royal Rumble '95",
        "description": "On This week's Something To Wrestle With Bruce Prichard, Bruce and Conrad discuss the 1995 Royal Rumble! Hear all about the Rumble in the \"New Generation\" era! Opening the show was one of the great sleeper matches in WWE history, as Razor Ramon defends the Intercontinental Championship against Jeff Jarrett! A not so fondly remembered match between the Undertaker and IRS follows, plus WWE Champion Diesel has his first high profile title defense, against the former champion Bret Hart. In a tournament final to crown new WWE Tag Team Champions, The 1-2-3 Kid and Bob Holly faced and defeated Bam Bam Bigelow and Tatanka to win the titles, which sent a raging Bigelow after Lawrence Taylor in a post match brawl that sets up the Wrestlemania XI main event!  And finally, the Rumble match itself, which showcases Shawn Michaels, but includes regular top names like The British Bulldog, Owen Hart, King Kong Bundy, Lex Luger, The Smoking Gunns, Crush, Bob Backlund and more! PLUS, Pamela Anderson!\nIf you have credit card debt or in a 30 year loan? Well, www.savewithconrad.com can help you get out of that pinch and save money at the same time! Head over to SaveWithConrad.com for a quick quote. \nCheck out long time show sponsor Blue Chew, the male enhancement chewable, at bluechew.com and get a free month supply for just $5 shipping with the code WRESTLE!",
