        "title": "Episode 134: December 22, 1997 RAW",
        "description": "Fire up the WWE Network and join Bruce and Conrad as they re-visit the WWF in a state of transition. The signature open still has the New Generation logo but boy are things different once the show starts. The WWF is coming under fire for \"going too far\" and there are even reported \"riots\" at live events. The top star can't wrestle so he fills his time investigating fake Santas... and defending future WWE Tag Team Champions. Plus the guys cover the Undertaker's health problems, the fall out from Bret Hart, the rumor and innuendo around Owen Hart sticking around, and so much more from the most interesting transition periods in the WWF!\n\n\n\n\nHave a question for our \"Foley Wins the Title\" episode next week? Head over to Facebook right now, facebook.com/SomethingToWrestle\n\n\n\n\nThe polls are back! Cast your \"Royal Rumble\" vote now @prichardshow\n\n\n\n\nSAN DIEGO is getting a live show! Tickets are on sale now at BrucePrichard.com for that show, Colorado Springs, Phoenix, and Connecticut!\n\n\n\n\nOver spend this holiday season? Save Yourself Some Money: www.SaveWithBruce.com\n\n\n\n\nGet a Brand New House with NO MONEY DOWN at BrandNewHouse.com",
