        "title": "129: Mid-Atlantic Championship Wrestling 07-07-1984",
        "description": "Tony and Conrad take you back to when wrestling on television was RAW...and we are not talking about the three hour WWE show.  They take you back to Jim Crockett Promotions flagship show:  Mid-Atlantic Championship Wrestling.  The company had just aired its first Starrcade the November before and were about a year away from their first ever show on TBS.  From the dark arena, to the off center \"hard camera,\" there was nothing quite like a JCP show.  \nThe territories in pro wrestling were coming to an end and Mid-Atlantic Championship Wrestling was still one of the best.  Enjoy 1984. \nSupport us on Patreon, get this show early and ad free, plus TONS of BONUScontent: http://patreon.com/WHWMonday\n Like us on Facebook: http://facebook.com/WHWMonday \n \nCheck out all the new cool merchandise at BoxOfGimmicks.com (http://boxofgimmicks.com/)\n Buy a shirt and Tony will call you (eventually!) at LoisRules.com (http://loisrules.com/)\n Subscribe to our YouTube channel: http://youtube.com/whw\nSave thousands at SaveCade.com (http://savecade.com/)  ",
