        "title": "117: WCW Monday Nitro REBOOT 04-10-2000",
        "description": "After a week of replays and clips, WCW Monday Nitro went back on the air live on April 10, 2000 to \"reboot\" the program.  It was a new direction of the company under both Eric Bischoff and Vince Russo.  It was an attempt to cross fiction and storylines with real life.  But now, looking back 19 years later, what actually transpired was muddled and confusing and helped WCW quickly down the  path of no-return.  Join Conrad and Tony for a look back at what seemed like a good idea at the time, but quickly became another painful chapter in the final year of the company.\nSupport us on Patreon, get this show early and ad free, plus TONS of BONUScontent: http://patreon.com/WHWMonday\nLike us on Facebook: http://facebook.com/WHWMonday\nCheck out the new koozies, hoodies, beach towels, and baby onesies at BoxOfGimmicks.com (http://boxofgimmicks.com/)\nBuy a shirt and Tony will call you (eventually!) at LoisRules.com (http://loisrules.com/)\nSubscribe to our YouTube channel: http://youtube.com/whw\nSave thousands at SaveCade.com (http://savecade.com/)\nGet Starrcast a la carte at fite.tv (http://fite.tv/)",
